LINE.Text: Groin injuries are a substantial problem among football players. Reduced hip adduction
strength is considered an important modifiable risk factor for groin injury.
The Adductor Strengthening Programme was performed
(from 18 teams) to increase hip adduction strength.
293 players from 16 teams performed regular football training
without the addition of the Adductor Strengthening Programme.
One exercise was utilised with three different progression levels.
Perform the programme at the highest level possible.
Drop down to a lower level if pain experienced >3 on a numeric rating scale
